l feedback: prototypes inform rule weights, and rule violations dynamically raise plausibility thresholds. Furthermore, we introduce *counterfactual prototype editing* during meta-learning episodes to simulate edge cases, improving calibration. This creates a more trustworthy, diagnosable system where NIL decisions are justified not only by distance but by semantic incoherence.

